WorkItem.Description: Rawr is showing the Tier 9 shoulders (ilvl 245) to be the highest burst HPS. It's showing them above even the 277 gear
WorkItem.Summary: [HealPriest] T9 Shoulders (245) showing as highest burst HPS

Comments.Message: See http://rawr.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=IDontUnderstandWhy&referringTitle=Documentation, especially about set bonuses. If that doesn't resolve your issue, edit this issue to follow the directions at the bottom of that page.
The 245 shoulders are sitting above the 258 shoulders on my screen.  Explain that one?

A) Lose the attitude
B) Open the Item Editor with both items, verify that the set names are spelled correctly and there are no extraneous spaces at the beginning, middle, or end. Also make sure the Socket Bonuses aren't missing (we have a problem in the current stuff where it's possible it may not have the socket bonus due to a data storage change on armory/wowhead).
C) Post your Character.xml File so we can open it and verify what you are seeing
D) There's a new chart under Buffs named 'Set Bonuses', check that and see where the set bonuses sit in comparison to each other
I'd like to see the .xml file where this happens, as it would let me see exactly what goes wrong.

Basically...
See http://rawr.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=IDontUnderstandWhy&referringTitle=Documentation, especially about set bonuses. If that doesn't resolve your issue, edit this issue to follow the directions at the bottom of that page.
